## Edit

Base on your comment:

&gt; I had missed a Z in my output. This doesn&#39;t give the Z at the end 

The output format include `Z` at the end, indicating the time is in the **UTC** time zone, in this case, you can use `OffsetDateTime` instead of `LocalDateTime` like this:

